-- Intel Hires Former Palm, Apple Executive for Smartphone Chip Development
-- Ian King
-- 2010-07-16T17:12:40Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-16/intel-hires-former-palm-apple-executive-for-smartphone-chip-development.html

          
          
             Intel Corp. , trying to get its chips
into the market for mobile phones, said it hired former Palm
Inc. executive  Mike Bell  to lead its smartphone product
development.  
 Bell was most recently vice president of the product
development team that created the Palm Pre and Palm Pixi
smartphones. Before that, he spent 16 years at  Apple Inc.  where
he contributed to the development of the iMac, Apple TV and
iPhone designs, Intel said today in an e-mailed statement.  
